did.abstract: Collection includes legislative records, governing documents, by-laws, student court cases, Greek policy, minutes and memos, records, and correspondence. freshmen register, homecoming and campaign posters, and constitutional convention records.

prefercite.head: Preferred citation
prefercite.p: Student Association records , University Archives, Special Collections Research Center, The George Washington University.

acqinfo.head: Acquisition Information
acqinfo.p: Materials acquired through transfers from the Student Association and from donations by individual alumni, as noted at the series level.

userestrict.head: Restrictions on Use
userestrict.p: Some material may be copyrighted or restricted. It is the patron's obligation to determine and satisfy copyright or other case restrictions when publishing or otherwise distributing materials found in the collections.

bioghist.head: Historical or Biographical Note
bioghist.p: Prior to the Student Association, the student governing body was the student council. The Student Association was established in April 1976. Membership included all full-time, part-time, graduate, professional and undergraduate students who were registered for academic credit. Today, the Student Association is made up of the executive, senate and judicial branches.

scopecontent.head: Collection Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: Materials in this collection include legislative records, governing documents, by-laws, student court cases, Greek policy, Marvin Center, athletics, budget, Senate minutes and memos. The collection also includes senate finance, reports to the Board of Trustees, Senate-elect meetings, senate meetings, roll call votes, senate administrative records, Tony Sayegh's records, Eric Daleo's records, correspondence, minutes, Mortar board, constitution membership logs, scrapbook, brochures, freshmen register, homecoming and campaign posters, and alumnus Barry Epstein's Constitutional Convention papers. The collection covers the years 1935-2005. Note: Not all series are processed. Ask staff for assistance.

arrangement.head: Collection Organization
arrangement.p: Organized into 11 series: Mortar Board society, Freshmen register, Posters, Photo directory, Student Association files, Meeting minutes, Student Association files, Student government records, Barry Epstein Constitutional Convention and Student Association papers, Joint Committee election records, and Kuyomars "Q" Golparvar collection of student association records.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series consists of Mortar Board (Hour Glass society) constitution, by-laws, oath, membership log, meeting minutes, scrapbook, banner, and brochures. The materials range in date from 1941-76.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series consists of the freshmen register, which listed incoming freshman and photos of them. The materials range in date from 1970-98.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series consists of a Student Association homecoming poster and campaign posters. The materials range in date from 1994-95.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series consists of a photo directory of new students, including transfers. The materials range in date from1966-67. This was the predecessor of the freshmen register.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series consists of legislative records, governing documents, by-laws, student court cases, greek policy, Marvin Center, budget records, senate minutes, memos, audio tapes. The materials range in date from 1991-2000.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series contains invitations, guides, a bookmark, brochures, correspondence, programs, memorandums, newsletters, stickers, reports, telegram, press releases, and posters. They range in date from 1935 to 2005. They materials concern the student government, the Student Association (SA), Student Council, the Student Council's Planning Commission, the Student Union, the history of the student government, elections, abolishment of the student government, student government officers, student political parties (left, center, right, service), communism, fascism, "The Left Party Speaks", "The Frontier: an independent journal of student opinion", the student government's constitution, the All-University Assembly, the Governing Board, the Operations Board of the University Center, an All University Government, organizational chart, priorities, services, charters, "GW Updates", "SA Update", SA Presidents, the Center for Academic Evaluation, and other activities.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series contains correspondence, reports, memos, notes, agendas, publicity, and other documents created and collected by George Washington University alumnus Barry Epstein as a member of the George Washington University Constitutional Convention in 1975 and 1976. The materials document the efforts of students to reestablish student governance at the University, and the founding of the Student Association. Records date between 1971 and 1977.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series contains of records generated and collected by former President of the Student Body (1997-1998) Kuyomars "Q" Golparvar. Materials include GW student association records, Constitutional Convention records, Budget Advisory Team records and other materials amassed by Golparvar. Many of the records predate his actual involvement with the GW student association; he collected and preserved them during his tenure.
